context: Although Brandenburg was a part of the <a0_0>Holy Roman Empire<a0_0/>, the Prussian lands were not within the Holy Roman Empire and were with the administration by the <a1_0>Teutonic Order<a1_0/> grandmasters under jurisdiction of the Emperor. In return for supporting Emperor <b8_0>Leopold I<b8_0/> in the War of the Spanish Succession, Elector <a2_0><b6_0>Frederick III<b6_0/><a2_0/> was allowed to crown himself "King in Prussia" in <b4_0><b5_0><b7_0>1701<b7_0/><b5_0/><b4_0/>. To differentiate from the larger entity, the former Duchy of Prussia became known as <a3_0>Altpreußen ("Old Prussia")<a3_0/>, the province of Prussia, or "East Prussia".
